      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_battery_mgr_1a557b206172fbde7a204eb0d2376b7f71" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void task</definition>
        <argsstring>(void) override</argsstring>
        <name>task</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_task_1a1951102653a5e603f2131b33d7636232">task</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Battery manager task function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>The function enters directly the endless loop and wait for messages. Task wakes up when a message is in the mailbox and read the message by calling mailbox read method which returns the pointer pElem to the message. All expected messages will be handled, in case of an unexpected message an error debug message will be triggered. Finally the message will be released by calling class <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> method free, if the pointer pElem is not explicitly set to 0. <linebreak/>
 <linebreak/>
<bold>Message Handling:</bold> <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>eTimerExpired: Unused, only debug message at debug level will be printed.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eAdcData: Received sensor data from AD converter task. Will forward as it is to data manager task mailbox.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eBattReport: Received report request frm power manager task. Battery manager request than an ADC report for the related ADC channels from AD converter task by calling member function reqAdcReport. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para><xrefsect id="todo_1_todo000006"><xreftitle>Todo</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>should be deleted: Battery manager not uses timers </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
        </inbodydescription>
